Package: discon
Type: Package
Title: Discourse Connectors Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2015-02-19
Authors@R: c(person("Tyler", "Rinker", email = "tyler.rinker@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Tyler Rinker <tyler.rinker@gmail.com>
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.2),
    qdap (>= 2.2.0)
Imports:
    ggplot2 (>= 1.0.0),
    qdapRegex (>= 0.2.0)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 0.9.1),
    qdapDictionaries (>= 1.0.2),
    qdapTools (>= 1.0.1)
LazyData: TRUE
Description: A collection of R tools for analysing discourse connectors in
    text.  Discourse connectors are cohesive devices that can be used to help
    identify themes within a text.  This package provides computational means
    of extracting various elements from the text that contain discourse
    connectors.  This can assist in qualitative analysis of discourse by
    identifying categories that may aide analysis (using the computer for
    efficiency and data coverage) towards generating themes.
